Defendant Shawn M McFallin in court with attorney Syovata Kanini Edari.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Deputy court clerk: LMS.

Statements made as to sentencing.  Additional statements by: Bishop Sedgwick D., Commisioner Hattie D.R., Shamara M. and Tamara D.

COUNT 1 & 2 - CONCURRENT:
Defendant sentenced to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction.  Huber privileges for work.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.

COUNT 3 & 4 - CONCURRENT:
Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction.  Huber privileges for work.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
* No spoof aps.
* Cognitive intervention programming.
   and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* No contact with the victim(s) without prior court/agent approval.  Any violation may result in additional charges.	
* Court order 50 hours of community service at a non-profit organization.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   and supervision fees or CIVIL JUDGMENT will be entered.

Case calendared for plea hearing.

Amended Information received and filed, amending Count 1 to Disorderly Conduct, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 947.01(1), a Class B Misdemeanor and adding Count 2; Disorderly Conduct, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 947.01(1), a Class B Misdemeanor, and Count 3 and 4; Computer Crimes (Access Data), contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 943.70(2)(a)(3), a Class A Misdemeanor.  Defense entered a plea of not guilty as to all counts.

AS TO AMENDED COUNT 1 AND ADDITIONAL COUNTS 2-4: Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead NO CONTEST and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum and Jury Instructions received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.
